They should be using preventer devices to cut swelling in the airways to stop an attack. Other versions deal with symptoms like coughing and wheezing. Asthma + Lung UK's poll found 21 percent have at least six reliever inhalers a year - triple the suggested number. The charity's Sarah Woolnough said: "Those with asthma are being let down by dismal rates of basic care caused by pressures on the NHS and outdated guidelines. "We need to see an urgent increase in yearly asthma reviews."